 This install applies to "Brian The Lion" Â© 1994 Psygnosis/Reflections.

 This install requires WHDLoad to be in the path. It can be found in the
 WHDLoad package.

 SUPPORTED VERSIONS:
 - original ECS release (supported by Carlo Pirri)
 - original AGA release (supported by Philippe Bovier)
 - Computer Combat pack (AGA) release (supported by Wolfgang Unger)

 ECS:
 
 The installed program requires 0.5 MB ChipMem and 1.5 MB OtherMem.
 It can be quit by pressing num '*' (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").

 AGA:
 
 The installed program requires 2.0 MB ChipMem and 3.5 MB OtherMem.
 It can be quit by pressing num '*' (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").


 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

 Version 2.0 (02.05.2021) done by JOTD:
 - joypad controls
 - optional jump with second button
 - adapted to whdload v17
 - improved & fixed trainer
 - quitkey in Way Forward level (ECS)
 - simplified level passwords: 2,3,4,5 and 6 for cheat
 - ECS version now uses 512k chipmem and fastmem instead of 1MB chip 

 
 Version 1.4 (15-Feb-2015) done by Wepl:
 - fixed OCS slave to work on 68000 (issue #3298)
 - added quitkey and enabled caches in OCS slave
 - new install script
 - many icons, manual and hints added

 Version 1.3 (05-Jul-2010) done by Wepl:
 - Access fault in underwater bonus stage removed
 - Access fault in Way Forward level (before boss appears) removed
 - Trainer added (set CUSTOM1=1 for unlimited lives and energy
   (except Way Forward level)
 - decruncher in fast ram
 - interrupt code improved

 Version 1.2 (28-Jun-2006) done by Bored Seal:
 - slave uses Fast RAM now (OCS)
 - disk access removed (OCS & AGA)
 
 Version 1.1 (01-May-2001) done by Bored Seal:
 - another AGA version supported (thanks Philippe)

 Version 1.0 (27-Mar-2001) done by Bored Seal:
 - first public release
 - Manual protection removed
 - NI/ROM icon (created by JHZ)
 - Quit option (your default key)

joypad controls:

- red: fire
- blue: jump (if option is set)
- play: pause (except in Way Forward level)
- fwd+bwd: quit game (except in Way Forward level, ESC doesn't work either!)
- fwd+bwd+yellow: quit to workbench (during game except in Way Forward level)

Original level codes:

The Spooky Ruins sXr7vgqaGP  (or 2)
The Way Forward	 sXqkKgqaGd  (or 3)
Graveyard	     sXqkKgqaGI  (or 4)
Eeek!	         sXqkK0KaGU  (or 5)

Enter "Mr*Pumpkin" (now just "6") as a password in the AGA version of the game.
The screen will flash to confirm correct code entry.

Then, press [Caps Lock] and one of the following keys to activate the
corresponding cheat function.

Effect 	Key
Nine hit points	 H
Nine lives	L
Nine of each power-up and nine credits 	J
999 gems	K
Full map 	O
Unknown	F
Unknown	D

Note: For the ECS version, enter "Mrs*Turnip" as a password or just "6" :)

